snippet: The review suggests that the first to sign up through the new insurance marketplaces were more likely to face serious health problems than those who get coverage through their employer.
abstract: Study by pharmacy-benefits manager Express Scripts provides much-anticipated look at population that signed up for coverage under new health care law; review suggests that early enrollees face more serious health problems and are older than those covered by their employer.
lead_paragraph: The review suggests that the first to sign up through the new insurance marketplaces were more likely to face serious health problems than those who get coverage through their employer.

headline.main: Study Finds Sicklier Enrollees in Earliest Stage of Health Law
headline.print_headline: Study Looks at Earliest Health Law Enrollees
